127
00:07:15,508 --> 00:07:16,888
to give them the rules up front.

128
00:07:16,888 --> 00:07:19,709
This is something you guys can definitely learn

129
00:07:19,709 --> 00:07:20,689
from my mistakes.

130
00:07:20,689 --> 00:07:24,089
So you want to have a contract at the very beginning.

131
00:07:24,089 --> 00:07:25,450
You can Google free templates.

132
00:07:25,450 --> 00:07:27,890
You don't have to hire a lawyer or spend any money.

133
00:07:27,890 --> 00:07:29,831
Just Google it and edit it just a little bit.

134
00:07:29,831 --> 00:07:33,631
You want to have the expectations up front.

135
00:07:33,631 --> 00:07:37,112
You want to tell them they need to work x hours per week.

136
00:07:37,857 --> 00:07:41,858
And they need to deliver in this type of way.

137
00:07:41,858 --> 00:07:43,419
They need to communicate.

138
00:07:43,419 --> 00:07:48,661
They must check in once every two days or three days.

139
00:07:48,661 --> 00:07:50,182
You need to tell them what's up.

140
00:07:50,182 --> 00:07:51,803
And this is where management comes in.

141
00:07:51,803 --> 00:07:54,064
You really need to be strict on this, especially

142
00:07:54,064 --> 00:07:56,445
at the beginning, because that's what sets the template.

143
00:07:56,445 --> 00:07:57,585
You don't want to be stepped on.

144
00:07:57,585 --> 00:07:59,506
You need to give them deadlines.

145
00:07:59,506 --> 00:08:01,087
At the beginning, you're not going

146
00:08:01,087 --> 00:08:03,528
to know what the deadlines are.

147
00:08:03,528 --> 00:08:05,849
You're going to say, oh, I have no idea how long this takes

148
00:08:05,849 --> 00:08:06,189
to make.

149
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,862
But what you're going to do is you're going to make a deadline anyway.

150
00:08:08,862 --> 00:08:09,402
You're going to guess.

151
00:08:09,402 --> 00:08:14,086
So you're going to say, three days, two weeks, it doesn't matter.

152
00:08:14,086 --> 00:08:16,848
Eventually, you'll start to learn how long things should take.

153
00:08:16,848 --> 00:08:19,450
And if they need to extend it, they'll tell you.

154
00:08:19,450 --> 00:08:23,753
This is also a good way to see if you can trust your employees.

155
00:08:23,753 --> 00:08:26,395
Because if you're working remotely like I am,

156
00:08:26,395 --> 00:08:31,419
then you've never met these people before.

157
00:08:31,419 --> 00:08:33,680
And that's where it comes to trials.

158
00:08:34,188 --> 00:08:37,329
Trials, what you can do is when you hire someone new,

159
00:08:37,329 --> 00:08:40,470
especially remotely, give them a 30 day trial.

160
00:08:40,470 --> 00:08:43,890
When you have 30 days, you can make sure

161
00:08:43,890 --> 00:08:47,491
that they perform exactly the way you want them to perform.

162
00:08:47,491 --> 00:08:51,152
And if something goes wrong, you could say, sorry guys,

163
00:08:51,152 --> 00:08:52,852
that's the end of the trial.

164
00:08:52,852 --> 00:08:53,912
This was a trial run.

165
00:08:53,912 --> 00:08:57,373
It also gives you sort of an excuse

166
00:08:57,373 --> 00:08:59,173
to be sort of hard on them.

167
00:08:59,173 --> 00:09:00,933
Because the beginning is everything.

168
00:09:02,495 --> 00:09:05,536
And that's how you can tell if you trust them or not.

169
00:09:05,536 --> 00:09:07,517
Communication is the most important,

170
00:09:07,517 --> 00:09:08,938
especially for remote teams.

171
00:09:08,938 --> 00:09:11,439
But even if you're in person, it's remote.

172
00:09:11,439 --> 00:09:13,419
Communication is top key.

173
00:09:13,419 --> 00:09:17,181
So Discord is what we use as the number one.

174
00:09:17,181 --> 00:09:19,942
So Discord has really changed our development cycle

