00:10:25,685 --> 00:10:27,845
with different priority levels and then drag it to done.

195
00:10:27,845 --> 00:10:29,085
It's pretty satisfying to see done.

196
00:10:32,304 --> 00:10:38,649
So trust is a big deal and that's why trials are really important.

197
00:10:38,649 --> 00:10:40,870
You want to keep your promises.

198
00:10:40,870 --> 00:10:47,435
And if you can't keep a promise, that's the point of the communication.

199
00:10:47,435 --> 00:10:52,659
So if you feel like you're starting to become sick, give a warning to the team.

200
00:10:52,659 --> 00:10:57,142
If you're coming up on a deadline and you don't think it's realistic, tell them.

201
00:10:57,142 --> 00:10:59,384
Everyone can be very...

202
00:11:00,407 --> 00:11:05,089
Very forgiving. As long as you communicate, then everything is under control.

